10.2
log
@Added $Id$ tag.
@
text
@Release Notes for the TreadMarks(tm) extension to support LoadLeveler. 

This distribution includes two versions of the TreadMarks library.
They are both in ./lib.rs6k:

libTmk_udp.a	is the standard TreadMarks library.  This version runs
		on SP2 nodes that allow interactive logins.  This is
		useful for development and debugging.

libTmk_udp_ll.a is the extended version of TreadMarks library that
		runs in EITHER interactive mode like the standard
		TreadMarks library OR in batch mode under LoadLeveler.
		Furthermore, it is capable of autosensing whether it
		was started by LoadLeveler or by an interactive shell. 

		Under LoadLever, the interactive debugging and display
		options are disabled.  Since LoadLeveler determines
		which hosts are used, the .Tmkrc file and the "-h"
		command line directive are ignored.

		This version of TreadMarks still uses the UDP/IP
		protocol through sockets.  The LoadLeveler command
		file determines whether TreadMarks uses Ethernet or
		the high-speed switch.  (Please see the sample command
		file below.)  We are testing a version of TreadMarks
		that uses the PE/MPL user-space CSS directly.  This
		will be released in the near future. 

To make the LoadLeveler version of a sample application, run "make"
in the application directory, "./apps/?/bin.rs6k".

What follows is a LoadLeveler command file that will run the barrier
test program (./apps/test/bin.rs6k/barrier.udp_ll) on 4 processors
using the high speed switch at the Cornell Theory Center.  Command
files for other applications and/or installations will be similar.
Please refer to your site's configuration documents for details such
as the available job classes. 

#!/bin/ksh
#@@ job_name = barrier
#@@ class = small_short
#@@ requirements = (Adapter == "hps_ip")
#@@ data_limit = 50mb
#@@ initialdir = .
#@@ environment = COPY_ALL
#@@ output = Log.$(cluster).$(process).out
#@@ error = Log.$(cluster).$(process).err
#@@ job_type = parallel
#@@ min_processors = 4
#@@ max_processors = 4
#@@ queue
barrier.udp_ll

$Id: ReleaseNotes.LoadLeveler,v 10.2 1997/03/18 21:03:24 alc Exp $
@


