9.5
log
@*** empty log message ***
@
text
@d1 1
a1 2
Note that there are two versions of the TreadMarks Library 
in lib.rs6k:
d3 50
a52 31
libTmk_udp.a    is the standard TreadMarks.  This version can
  be run on SP2 nodes that allow interactive logins.  This is
  useful for development and debugging, but performance can suffer
  because interactive nodes are usually shared with other users.

libTmk_udp_ll.a  is a version of TreadMarks that can run in batch mode
  under LoadLeveler.  

  In batch mode debugging and display options are inappropriate, so
  they are disabled.

  This version is still using the UDP/IP communication protocol.
  If the LoadLeveler command file requests it, this version will
  use the IP over the high performance switch of the SP2.  We are
  testing a version that uses the PE/MPL user-space CSS directly.
  This will be released in the near future.

  This version expects LoadLeveler to provide the set of hosts
  on which to run.  Any use of a .Tmkrc file or -hhostname on 
  the command line are ignored.

  The maximum number of nodes in this demo version is 8.

To
make the LoadLeveler versions run "make ll" in the directories
"Tmkll.demo/apps/*/bin.rs6k".

In the directory Tmkll.demo/apps/test/bin.rs6k/LoadL.commands, there
are LoadLeveler command files that were used to run the test programs
at the Cornell Theory Center.  You can use them as examples for
creating your own.
@


