  There is one  small extension beyond the standard version 0.9.3 
  described elsewhere --    
  The standard version must be started on the first host mentioned.
  This version can generally be started from any of the hosts specified, 
  either on the command line or in a .Tmkrc file.

libTmk_lludp.a  is a version of TreadMarks that can run in batch mode
